<TITLE> Aston Villa match marred by coin-throwing incident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)  Aston Villa are investigating an incident in Saturday's 0-0 Premier League draw with Portsmouth, after an assistant referee was injured by a coin thrown by a supporter. "It is just unacceptable and there's no place for it in the game whatsoever," Villa manager Martin O'Neill told the club website (www.avfc.premiumtv.co.uk). Phil Sharp was hit by a 50 pence piece and received a cut above his right eye. If caught, the fan will be banned from the Midlands club for life. "I turned to the fourth official and he told me there were four minutes of added time and then the next thing you know, the linesman is on the floor after being hit by a coin," O'Neill added. The Villa website also stated that the English Football Association (FA) will focus on finding the culprit and not punishing the clu
